      "side": 1,
      "message": "Thank you very much for putting this CL together - this is really great and I hope to leverage the new functionality for implementing Clippy support in Chromium.\n\n----------------------------\n\n# Manual testing\n\nI have tried using `validations` implemented by this CL to extend Clippy support in Chromium - see: https://crrev.com/c/7516242.  I see that `.ninja` files have validation edges now - e.g.:\n\n```\n$ find out/rel -type f -name \u0027*.ninja\u0027 | \\\n    xargs grep qr_code_generator_ffi_glue_clippy\n...\nout/rel/obj/components/qr_code_generator/qr_code_generator_ffi_glue.ninja:build obj/components/qr_code_generator/libqr_code_generator_ffi_glue_3f54a341.rlib ... |@ phony/components/qr_code_generator/qr_code_generator_ffi_glue_clippy\n...\n```\n\nAnd it seems that the new edge works in the way I would expect.  I tried testing this edge in the following way:\n\n* I\u0027ve inserted an artificial `time.sleep(25)` delay into `build/rust/gni_impl/clippy_wrapper.py`\n* I\u0027ve inserted a Clippy violation into `components/qr_code_generator/qr_code_generator_ffi_glue.rs` by adding `.into()` to `*out_qr_size \u003d qr_code.width().into();`\n* I\u0027ve run `autoninja -C out/rel components_unittests` expecting that the building/linking of `components_unittests` will **not** depend on Clippy results.  And therefore that `out/rel/components_unittests` will be present afterwards.  And this is indeed what happened.",
      "revId": "a35731d165b12585f0ff737a0dea398f6474f193",
      "serverId": "c360c8e5-7aa8-3905-a7a0-810934766dac"
    },
    {
