      "writtenOn": "2026-01-26T20:07:13Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "# Context\n\nClippy is set up in https://crrev.com/c/7516242 in the following way:\n\n* `//components/qr_code_generator:qr_code_generator_ffi_glue_clippy` target depends via `deps` on `//components/qr_code_generator:qr_code_generator_ffi_glue` target (e.g. the latter will generate `.rustflags.json` that will be consumed by `clippy_wrapper.py` to ensure that `clippy-driver` is invoked with the same command-line flags (e.g. `--cfg\u003dfoo`) as `rustc`\n* `//components/qr_code_generator:qr_code_generator_ffi_glue` lists `//components/qr_code_generator:qr_code_generator_ffi_glue_clippy` in `validations`.\n\n`validations` is not a \"real\" dependency - the result of the validation is not needed by `//components/qr_code_generator:qr_code_generator_ffi_glue`.  Therefore IMO `validations` edges should not be considered in cycle detection.\n\n# Problem\n\n`AddDeps` call added here results in the following `gn` error after https://crrev.com/c/7516242:\n\n```\nERROR Dependency cycle:\n  //build/rust/allocator:allocator -\u003e\n  //build/rust/allocator:allocator_clippy -\u003e\n  //build/rust/allocator:allocator\n```\n\n# Discussion\n\nI can avoid the problem by removing the new `AddDeps` call.  But...\n\n* I don\u0027t know if removing the new `AddDeps` call may cause other issues\n* I am not sure how to add a regression test that verifies that `validations` edges do not participate in cycle detection",
      "range": {
